{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κηρός</b>, ὁ, <br /> <b>bees-wax</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.48, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 1.27, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>honeycomb</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 20.27; εὐπλαστότερον κηροῦ 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 588d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; used as a cosmetic, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Epistulae” 22 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; in encaustic painting, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42 (1).102.272 (Epid., 4th c.BC), 14.1320;\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] for writing tablets, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 736.16 (1st c.AD)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>], etc.: hence λόγους εἰς γραμμάτιον καὶ κηρὸν ἐρχομένους [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Libanius Sophista “Epistulae” 886.1. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>sealing-wax</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 21. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> κ. Τυρρηνικός <b>white wax</b> used in medicine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 13.411, 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 1.70. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>plural</i> κηροί <b>wax tapers</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Heliodorus Scriptor Eroticus 9.11. (Panhellenic η, “IG” 42.[same place], Theoc. [prev. cited], compare κήρινος, κηρόδετος, κηροχυτέω\">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; Latin <i>cera.</i>)","strongNumber":"G8008","accentedUnicode":"κηρός","shortDef":"beeswax","mediumDef":"beeswax","stepGloss":"beeswax","stepTransliteration":"kēros","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}